It's also time for planting, so we'll learn about an urban agriculture program in Wheat Ridge. We'll also visit the fascinating Butterfly Pavilion, on Connected Colorado.

title: The Changing World of Film Festivals
label: The Changing World of Film Festivals
description: Like just about everything else in the world of cinema, film festivals have undergone major changes during the past several decades. The Denver Film Festival's 40th anniversary provides an excellent opportunity to look at their evolution. Panel moderator Robert Denerstein will lead the discussion, posing questions about the future of film festivals in the face of radical technological and cultural challenges with panelists: Ron Henderson (Denver Film Festival Founder), Randi Kleiner (SeriesFest Founder), Brit Withey (Denver Film Society Artistic Director), and Landon Zakheim (Overlook Film Festival Founder)

title: Thornton Paint-A-Thon 2014
label: Thornton Paint-A-Thon 2014
description:
Co-hosted by the city of Thornton and Brothers Redevelopment, the Paint-A-Thon program paints the homes of low-income elderly and disabled homeowners at no cost to them.

The next Thornton Paint-A-Thon event will be held in Summer 2014 and there are many ways to become a part of this Thornton community event.  Become a volunteer, make a donation, or apply for assistance.

For more information visit www.cityofthornton.net
Or contact Neighborhood Services at 303-538-7600 or neighbor@cityofthornton.net
